Package org.logevents.impl

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    LogEventFilter  
    LogEventGenerator
    Internal interface that is used by all calls to Logger.error(java.lang.String), Logger.warn(java.lang.String), Logger.info(java.lang.String), Logger.debug(java.lang.String) and Logger.trace(java.lang.String).
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ConditionalLogEventFilter
    A LogEventObserver that forwards all log events to a delegate observer if they have a log level equal to or more severe than the ConditionalLogEventFilter.minimumThreshold or if there is a MDC variable on the thread which fulfills a configured logging rule.
    ConditionalLogEventGenerator
    Forwards the log event to it's ConditionalLogEventGenerator.observer if LogEventPredicate.test() returns true.
    JavaUtilLoggingAdapter
    An adapter from java.util.logging to LogEvents.
    LevelThresholdFilter  
    LoggerDelegator
    Internal implementation of SLF4J Logger.
    NeverLogEventFilter  
    SLF4JServiceProviderImpl
